parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Front Airbags to Deploy
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of front airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants may not receive the necessary protection to prevent harm.
symptoms: The front airbags do not deploy in a crash
resulting in occupants sustaining injuries or fatalities

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic booster can cause a loss of brake pressure, leading to extended stopping distances, increased risk of accidents, and potential loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Unusual noise from the left side of the dash panel when the brakes are applied
delayed brake boost assist after the vehicle has been parked for a period of time
brake pedal goes all the way to the floor
strange noise from under the dash while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake wear can cause reduced braking performance, increased stopping distances, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pads must be changed frequently
unusual screeching noise from the driver's side of the vehicle when it is at rest
and when the brakes are pressed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake caliper failure can cause a loss of brake pressure, leading to extended stopping distances, increased risk of accidents, and potential loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Retaining bolts on the driver's side front brake caliper fell out
brake caliper rotated and struck the inside of the wheel

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake line failure can cause a loss of brake pressure, leading to extended stopping distances, increased risk of accidents, and potential loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: Front brake lines failed upon frontal impact
brake lines broke at the point where the flexible rubber part of the line connects to the metal fitting that is attached to the inner fender well.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Master cylinder failure can cause a loss of brake pressure, leading to extended stopping distances, increased risk of accidents, and potential loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: master cylinder failure caused an accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft bolt can cause loss of power steering, damage to the crankshaft sensor, harmonic balancer, and timing belt, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: sudden loss of power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine oil leaks and sludge can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Failure of the oxygen sensor can cause poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
Failure of the air conditioning compressor can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stalling and Loss of Power
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling and loss of power can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
